<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,854,915]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,854,879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The characteristic shape of S 
<number box="[609,623,855,879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89" value="7.0">7</number>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[664,801,854,878]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kazakhus">
<emphasis box="[664,801,854,878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">C. kazakhus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the dense fringe of short hairs along its apical and lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[333,399,890,915]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="89">
Fig. 
<number box="[385,399,890,915]" pageId="8" pageNumber="89" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c) is unique and unmistakable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
