<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,418,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Bl = 7.0 mm. Head. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black except mandible dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long white, erect hairs. Malar area medially about 
<number box="[1199,1233,188,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x as long as width of mandible base, finely striate, matt and sparsely covered with short erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1119,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Fig. 
<number box="[1104,1119,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Antenna black, flagellum ventrally yellowish-brown. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc smooth and shiny between punctures; disc very sparsely punctate (i = 
<number box="[520,562,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
d) with small punctures. Mesoscutellum almost completely impunctate, with dense punctation on apical margin, surface smooth and shiny. Mesoscutum, mesoscutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, greyish-white erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1107,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Fig. 
<number box="[1092,1107,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Wings. Translucent; wing venation light yellow. Legs. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; apical and basal parts of tibiae and tarsi yellowish-brown. Vestiture greyish-white. Metasoma. Integument black except depressed apical tergal margins yellowish translucent (
<figureCitation box="[406,474,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Fig. 
<number box="[459,474,476,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terga densely covered with short appressed, yellowish-white hairs; T 
<number box="[1294,1304,476,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="1.0">1</number>
and disc of T 
<number box="[168,182,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="2.0">2</number>
additionally with abundant long erect hairs of the same colour; apical tergal hair bands narrow (
<figureCitation box="[1268,1336,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1336,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terga apically distinctly depressed. Terga with dense and fine punctation (i = 
<number box="[1014,1079,548,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1</number>
d), smooth and shiny between punctures (
<figureCitation box="[275,342,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,958,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[173,1417,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes kazakhus Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); d. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239800/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,342,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terminalia. Genitalia and S 
<number box="[686,701,584,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="7.0">7</number>
as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[885,956,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,295,1323]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,295,1323]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Colletes issykkuli Kuhlmann 2003, female: a. head; b. mesoscutum and mesoscutellum; c. metasomal terga 1 and 2. C. kozlovi Friese 1913, female: d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239798/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
Figs 
<number box="[941,956,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
c–d.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,824]" box="[199,418,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="90">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
